quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  30,42,"Say: ´Travel about the earth and see the final fate of those before. Most of them were idolaters.´"
  30,43,"So set your face firmly towards the True Deen, before a Day comes from Allah which cannot be turned back. On that Day they will be split up"
  30,44,Those who were kafir will find that their kufr was against themselves. Those who did right were making the way easy for themselves
  30,45,so that He can repay with His bounty those who had iman and did right actions. He certainly does not love the kafirun
  30,46,"Among His Signs is that He sends the winds bearing good news, to give you a taste of His mercy, and to make the ships run by His command, and to enable you to seek His bounty so that hopefully you will be thankful"
  30,47,"Before you We sent other Messengers to their people, and they too brought them the Clear Signs. We took revenge on those who did evil; and it is Our duty to help the muminun"
  30,48,"It is Allah who sends the winds which stir up clouds which He spreads about the sky however He wills. He forms them into dark clumps and you see the rain come pouring out from the middle of them. When He makes it fall on those of His slaves He wills, they rejoice"
  30,49,even though before He sent it down on them they were in despair
  30,50,"So look at the effect of the mercy of Allah, how He brings the dead earth back to life. Truly He is the One Who brings the dead to life. He has power over all things"